column2: 1. Consent I confirm that I am 18 years or older, currently enrolled or graduated in a university or tertiary institution in New Zealand, and I voluntarily consent to participate in this survey.
column9: I can recognise a phishing email or message when I see one.
column10: I know what two-factor authentication (2FA) is and why it is used.
column11: I understand what malware is and how it functions.
column12: I am familiar with what a Virtual Private Network (VPN) does.
column13: I know best practices for creating strong and secure passwords.
column14: I understand the risks of using public Wi-Fi without additional protections.
column15: I use a unique password for each of my important online accounts.
column16: I regularly update the software and applications on my devices.
column17: I enable two-factor authentication (2FA) on accounts whenever possible.
column18: I avoid clicking links or opening attachments from unknown or suspicious emails.
column19: I review app permissions and only allow access to what is necessary.
column20: I back up important files regularly to a secure location.
column21: I use a VPN or other protections when accessing public Wi-Fi for sensitive tasks.
column22: I feel confident in my ability to detect online scams and phishing attempts.
column23: I am concerned about the privacy and security of my personal information online.
column24: I believe cybersecurity knowledge is important for my academic and professional life.
column25: I believe my current online practices are sufficient to protect me from most cyber threats.
column26: I would attend a workshop on practical cybersecurity skills if my institution offered one.
column27: I have received formal cybersecurity training (e.g., course, workshop, or module) during my studies.
column28: My institution provides adequate information on how to stay safe online.
